menu "AMD SFH HID support"
	depends on PCI && ACPI

config AMD_SFH_HID
	tristate "AMD Sensor Fusion Hub"
	select HID
	help
	If you say yes to this option, support will be included for the AMD
	Sensor Fusion Hub.
	This driver will enable sensors functionality to user through HID
	framework. Basically this driver will get data from MP2 FW and
	provide that data to HID framework.
	MP2 which is an ARMÂ® Cortex-M4 core based co-processor to x86.

	This driver can also be built as modules. If so, the modules will
	be called amd-sfh-pci and amd-sfh-hid.

endmenu
